records.nl_statement: Suppose $k \geq 3, x, y \in \mathbb{R}^k, |x - y| = d > 0$, and $r > 0$. Prove that if $2r > d$, there are infinitely many $z \in \mathbb{R}^k$ such that $|z-x|=|z-y|=r$.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Topology Filter Real Complex TopologicalSpace Finset
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_1_16a
  (n : ℕ)
  (d r : ℝ)
  (x y z : EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n)) -- R^n
  (h₁ : n ≥ 3)
  (h₂ : ‖x - y‖ = d)
  (h₃ : d > 0)
  (h₄ : r > 0)
  (h₅ : 2 * r > d)
  : Set.Infinite {z : EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n) | ‖z - x‖ = r ∧ ‖z - y‖ = r} :=

records.nl_statement: Let $(p_n)$ be a sequence and $f:\mathbb{N}\to\mathbb{N}$. The sequence $(q_k)_{k\in\mathbb{N}}$ with $q_k=p_{f(k)}$ is called a rearrangement of $(p_n)$. Show that if $f$ is an injection, the limit of a sequence is unaffected by rearrangement.

  Tendsto (λ n => p (f n)) atTop (𝓝 a) :=

records.nl_statement: Prove that if $H$ is a nontrivial normal subgroup of the solvable group $G$ then there is a nontrivial subgroup $A$ of $H$ with $A \unlhd G$ and $A$ abelian.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Fintype Subgroup Set Polynomial Ideal
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_3_4_11 {G : Type*} [Group G] [IsSolvable G]
  {H : Subgroup G} (hH : H ≠ ⊥) [H.Normal] :
  ∃ A ≤ H, A ≠ ⊥ ∧ A.Normal ∧ ∀ a b : A, a*b = b*a :=
records.baseline_candidate:
theorem autoformalized_theorem_1913 {G : Type*} [Group G] [IsSolvable G]
  {H : Subgroup G} (hH : H ≠ ⊥) [H.Normal] :
